<Base
  title="Rights & License — SF6 Sensei"
  description="How SF6 Sensei handles rights and licensing: the data source (SuperCombo Wiki / CC-BY-SA), Capcom's rights, and the measures we take."
>
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h1>Rights & License</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: June 16, 2026</p>

      <p>
        SF6 Sensei is a fan-made, <strong>unofficial and non-commercial</strong> project with no
        affiliation or relationship to Capcom Co., Ltd. This page explains the source, license, and
        handling of rights for the data, along with the measures we take.
      </p>

      <div class="note">
        This page is not legal advice. Please confirm the latest guidelines and terms of each rights
        holder yourself.
      </div>

      <h2>1. Status of the frame data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          What this Service handles is <strong>factual information — the numbers (frame data) measured
          in-game</strong>. Facts such as game mechanics and numbers are generally understood not to
          be subject to copyright (the U.S. Copyright Office states that "the idea for a game, its
          rules, methods, and systems are not protected by copyright"; Japanese law has no clear
          precedent).
        </li>
        <li>
          That said, following industry custom (as with frame data wikis like Dustloop and Mizuumi),
          we treat the rights to the game's content as belonging to their respective rights holders.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Capcom's rights and the measures we take</h2>
      <p>
        "Street Fighter," character names, move names, and other names and elements related to the
        game are trademarks or copyrighted works of Capcom Co., Ltd. The Service respects the spirit
        of Capcom's guidelines and takes the following measures.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Stating it is unaffiliated and unofficial:</strong> the Service has no affiliation or relationship with Capcom and is not endorsed by it.</li>
        <li><strong>Non-commercial:</strong> the Service is not monetized. There is no advertising, billing, or paywall.</li>
        <li>
          <strong>No game assets:</strong>
          no game images, audio, sprites, or other assets are used. Character and move names are used
          solely for identification and reference.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Responding to takedown requests:</strong>
          upon a legitimate request from a rights holder, we will promptly delete or correct the
          content in question.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">
        <strong>Important:</strong>
        the above are measures we take; they do not guarantee "full compliance" with Capcom's Fan
        Content Guidelines or EULA. The form of providing frame data is open to interpretation. Before
        using or redistributing, please check the latest official information such as the
        <a href="https://www.capcom-games.com/en/fan-content-guidelines/">Capcom Fan Content Guidelines</a>.
      </div>

      <h2>3. Data source and CC-BY-SA</h2>
      <p>The frame data is sourced from the SuperCombo Wiki, used under the terms of Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike (CC-BY-SA).</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Source (original work):</strong>
          <a href="https://wiki.supercombo.gg/w/Street_Fighter_6">SuperCombo Wiki — Street Fighter 6 Frame Data</a>
          (data is fetched via the same operator's API at <code>srk.shib.live</code>)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>License:</strong> Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike (CC-BY-SA).
          <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/">creativecommons.org</a>
          (the exact version follows the SuperCombo Wiki's notice)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Statement of changes:</strong>
          the Service modifies the original data by removing wiki markup, structuring it into JSON,
          converting and normalizing frame values into numbers, and adding Japanese move names and aliases.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>ShareAlike:</strong>
          the frame data the Service provides is offered under the same CC-BY-SA as the source. When
          redistributing, maintain attribution, the license notice, the statement of changes, and
          inheritance under the same license.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Each MCP response also includes the source (source / license / fetch date), so attribution
        can be traced when quoting an answer.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Trademarks</h2>
      <p>
        Product, service, and company names mentioned on this page and in the Service are trademarks
        or registered trademarks of their respective owners. The Service uses them solely for
        identification and does not represent the respective rights holders.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For inquiries or takedown requests regarding rights and licensing, please reach out via <a
          href="https://github.com/RyoSogawa/sf6-sensei/issues">GitHub Issues</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
